 PRODUCTION DATA – Feb 1, 2021


**Bytes to be Included into the CRC Sum:**


•
 All frame header bytes have to be included into the header CRC6 sum. The CRC6 bits of the 3rd frame header byte have to 


be set to 0 when including this byte into the frame header CRC sum.


•
 All frame data bytes have to be included into the frame data CRC8 sum.


•
 In case of the single data word frame format, both data bytes have to be included into the CRC6 sum, while setting the 


CRC6 bits of the 2nd data byte to 0.


**CRC Calculation Example Code:**


All CRC calculations in used protocol are byte wise and LSB first.


The following C style example calculation routine can be used to add a data byte to the incremental CRC sum:


uint8_t crc_calc(uint8_t crc, uint8_t rev_poly, uint8_t byte) {


 uint8_t n;
 for(n = 0; n < 8; n++) {


 if ((crc ^ byte) & 1) {


 crc = (crc >> 1) ^ rev_poly;


 } else {


 crc = (crc >> 1);


 }
 byte >>= 1;


 }
 return crc;


}


For generation of the reverse polynomial, the following C style example routine can be used:


// generate reverse polynomial example:
// polynomial 0xA6 => 1010.0110.1 (including bit 0 which is 1) => 1.0100.1101 = 0x14D
// => reversed 1.0110.0101 = 0x165 => 1011.0010.1 => 0xB2 (LSB skipped)


uint8_t calc_rev_poly(uint8_t poly) {


 uint8_t rev_poly = 1;
 while (poly > 1) {


 rev_poly = (rev_poly << 1) | (poly & 1);
 poly >>= 1;


 }
 return rev_poly;


}


For further details on CRC calculation, the used polynomial notation and best polynomial selection, please see Philip Koop-
man's publications (Associate Professor at Carnegie Mellon University).


