**8.4 Device Access via the Bus Interface**


**8.4.1 Bus Interface Memory Map**


The device configuration and status values can be accessed through the communication bus interface.


The following table defines the virtual bus memory view map. The given base address and area size values reflect the internal
16 bit organization of the values, which are all 10 bit values and therefore the bus memory areas are treated as 16 bit value 
structures with an address increment of 2 between adjacent values. When transferred via the communication interface, the 
constant register address LSB (which is always 0) has to be skipped and must not be included in the communication frame 
register address field.
